title.narrative: OUTPUT 1.2: MCH/PMTCT

description.narrative: Output 1.2 MCH/PMTCT: HIV Regional and national stakeholders have increased evidence, capacity and effective platforms to develop and monitor policies and programmes that address inequities in maternal, neonatal and child health, the elimination of HIV vertical transmission in development, fragile and humanitarian contexts., which contributes to Child Health, Hiv Prevention, Immunization, Maternal And Newborn Health, Treatment And Care Of Children Living With Hiv. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: OUTCOME 1: Girls, boys and adolescents in LAC benefit from equitable policies and programmes to guarantee their health, wellbeing and full development.
